   exp:'Statement 1: INCORRECT — India\'s exports in 2004-05 grew at over 20% in rupee terms compared to 2003-04, not below 10%. The mid-2000s saw strong export growth driven by engineering goods, gems & jewellery, and petroleum products. Statement 2: INCORRECT — India\'s share in world merchandise exports in 2005 was approximately 0.8–1%, NOT 2%. India\'s share crossed 2% only after 2010-11. Both statements are incorrect.'},

  {id:8,yr:'2004',topic:'Trade Deficit',
   text:'Assertion (A): For the first time, India had no trade deficit in the year 2002-03.\nReason (R): For the first time, India\'s exports crossed worth $50 billion in 2002-03.\n\n[2004]',
