  {id:9,yr:'2003',topic:'Petroleum & Export Growth',
   text:'Consider the following statements: [2003]\n1. India\'s import of crude and petroleum products in 2001-02 accounted for about 27% of India\'s total imports.\n2. During 2001-02, India\'s exports had increased by 10% compared to the previous year.\n\nWhich is/are correct?',
