   exp:'Statement 1: INCORRECT — India ranks second in world fruit production (after China). China has been the world\'s largest fruit producer for decades. India is among the top producers of mangoes, bananas, and citrus, but ranks second overall, not first. Statement 2: INCORRECT — India is not the second largest exporter of tobacco. Brazil is the world\'s largest tobacco exporter; India ranks lower (around 3rd–5th). Both statements are incorrect, making "Neither 1 nor 2" the answer.'},

  {id:11,yr:'2003',topic:'Software & IT Exports',
   text:'Consider the following statements: [2003]\n1. In the last five years, Indian software exports have increased at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of about 60%.\n2. The software and service industry in India registered an overall growth of about 28% in rupee terms during 2001-02.\n\nWhich is/are correct?',
