   exp:'Assertion A is TRUE — India\'s exports in 2001-02 did decline by approximately -2.17% (confirmed UPSC data), primarily due to global slowdown post-9/11 attacks and the dot-com bust affecting demand. Reason R is also TRUE — iron & steel, coffee, textiles, and marine products all recorded negative export growth in 2001-02. However, R is NOT the complete/correct explanation because the decline was also caused by external factors like global recession, dollar appreciation, and reduced demand — not just these specific commodity declines. So R is true but does not fully explain A.'},

  {id:13,yr:'2003',topic:'EXIM Policy & GATT',
   text:'Assertion (A): The new EXIM Policy is liberal, market-oriented and favours global trade.\nReason (R): GATT has played a significant role in the liberalisation of the economy.\n\n[2003]',
