   ans:1,
   exp:'Assertion A is TRUE — India\'s EXIM Policy post-1991 liberalisation became progressively more liberal, market-oriented, and trade-friendly. Import licensing was reduced, quantitative restrictions removed, and exports were incentivised. Reason R is also TRUE — GATT (General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade) and its successor WTO played a major role in global trade liberalisation. India, as a GATT/WTO member, aligned its trade policy accordingly. However, R is not the CORRECT explanation of A — India\'s EXIM Policy liberalisation was primarily driven by India\'s own 1991 economic reforms (LPG reforms), not just GATT. Both are true but R doesn\'t explain A.'},

